      "instruction": "<p>Once everything's been cooking for 30 min, boil half a kettle</p><p>Cut your <strong>tomato[es]</strong> in half</p><p>Add the<strong> tomato halves</strong>, cut-side up, to a baking tray with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and season with<strong> salt</strong></p><p>Drizzle over <strong>half</strong> your <strong>balsamic vinegar </strong>(save the rest for later!)</p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 12-15 min or until tender – this is your <strong>roasted</strong> <strong>balsamic tomato</strong></p>",
